article.description:
Darnell Harris made two free throws
with no time showing on the clock in the fourth overtime to give
LaSalle a 107-106 victory over Central Connecticut Saturday.
article.headline: La Salle edges Central Conn. in four OTs
article.linkText: Four overtimes later, La Salle edges Central Connecticut
article.story:
NEW BRITAIN, Conn. (AP) -- Darnell Harris made two free throws
with no time showing on the clock in the fourth overtime to give
La Salle a 107-106 victory over Central Connecticut on Sunday.

	   Central (4-4) led 106-102 after Tristan Blackwood made two free
throws with 20.9 seconds left, but Steven Smith (41 points) hit a
3-pointer with 8.6 seconds remaining to pull the Explorers within
one.

	   After CCSU failed to score, Harris raced down the floor and took
a shot from just outside the arc, but drew a foul with no time
left. He missed the first foul shot, but made the next two to seal
the win for LaSalle (6-0).

	   Javier Mojica's 3-pointer with 2:56 left in the fourth overtime
capped a 6-0 Central run and gave the Blue Devils a 100-95 lead.
Smith hit a turnaround in the lane, then later scored again to tie
the game at 100 with 1:32 left.

	   Blackwood scored on an offensive rebound, then later made two
free throws to give the Blue Devils a 104-100 lead.

	   Mojica forced the game into the fourth overtime with a jumper
from the left elbow with 4.4 seconds left in the third extra
session.

	   Blackwood led Central with 28 points and nine assists. Justin
Chiera added 21 points for the Blue Devils, while Obie Nwadike had
19 points and 18 rebounds.

	   Smith also had 10 rebounds, while Harris finished with 16 points
for LaSalle.
